{"title": "LDAP", "source": "active-directory", "source_label": "Active Directory", "path": "Active Directory/LDAP", "html": "<h2 id=\"ldap-enumeration\">LDAP Enumeration</h2>\n<p>LDAP queries for enumerating Active Directory objects from both Linux and Windows.</p>\n<hr />\n<h2 id=\"from-linux-ldapsearch\">From Linux (ldapsearch)</h2>\n<h3 id=\"enumerate-password-policy\">Enumerate Password Policy</h3>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code>ldapsearch<span class=\"w\"> </span>-h<span class=\"w\"> </span>&lt;dc-ip&gt;<span class=\"w\"> </span>-x<span class=\"w\"> </span>-b<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">&quot;DC=&lt;DOMAIN&gt;,DC=LOCAL&quot;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-s<span class=\"w\"> </span>sub<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">&quot;*&quot;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>grep<span class=\"w\"> </span>-m<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-B<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">10</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>pwdHistoryLength\n</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"enumerate-all-users-samaccountname-only\">Enumerate All Users (SamAccountName Only)</h3>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code>ldapsearch<span class=\"w\"> </span>-h<span class=\"w\"> </span>&lt;dc-ip&gt;<span class=\"w\"> </span>-x<span class=\"w\"> </span>-b<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">&quot;DC=&lt;DOMAIN&gt;,DC=LOCAL&quot;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-s<span class=\"w\"> </span>sub<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">&quot;(&amp;(objectclass=user))&quot;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>grep<span class=\"w\"> </span>sAMAccountName:<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>cut<span class=\"w\"> </span>-f2<span class=\"w\"> </span>-d<span class=\"s2\">&quot; &quot;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<hr />\n<h2 id=\"from-windows-adsi-ad-module\">From Windows (ADSI / AD Module)</h2>\n<h3 id=\"list-all-ad-groups-via-ldap-filter\">List All AD Groups via LDAP Filter</h3>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nb\">Get-ADObject</span> <span class=\"n\">-LDAPFilter</span> <span class=\"s1\">&#39;(objectClass=group)&#39;</span> <span class=\"p\">|</span> <span class=\"nb\">select </span><span class=\"n\">cn</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"list-disabled-users\">List Disabled Users</h3>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nb\">Get-ADUser</span> <span class=\"n\">-LDAPFilter</span> <span class=\"s1\">&#39;(userAccountControl:1.2.840.113556.1.4.803:=2)&#39;</span> <span class=\"p\">|</span> <span class=\"nb\">select </span><span class=\"n\">name</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"count-users-in-an-ou\">Count Users in an OU</h3>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">Get-ADUser</span> <span class=\"n\">-SearchBase</span> <span class=\"s2\">&quot;OU=Employees,DC=&lt;DOMAIN&gt;,DC=LOCAL&quot;</span> <span class=\"n\">-Filter</span> <span class=\"p\">*).</span><span class=\"n\">count</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"find-computers-by-hostname-pattern\">Find Computers by Hostname Pattern</h3>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nb\">Get-ADComputer</span> <span class=\"n\">-Filter</span> <span class=\"s2\">&quot;DNSHostName -like &#39;SQL*&#39;&quot;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"get-all-administrative-groups\">Get All Administrative Groups</h3>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nb\">Get-ADGroup</span> <span class=\"n\">-Filter</span> <span class=\"s2\">&quot;adminCount -eq 1&quot;</span> <span class=\"p\">|</span> <span class=\"nb\">select </span><span class=\"n\">Name</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"find-admin-users-without-kerberos-pre-auth\">Find Admin Users Without Kerberos Pre-Auth</h3>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nb\">Get-ADUser</span> <span class=\"n\">-Filter</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"n\">adminCount</span> <span class=\"o\">-eq</span> <span class=\"s1\">&#39;1&#39;</span> <span class=\"o\">-and</span> <span class=\"n\">DoesNotRequirePreAuth</span> <span class=\"o\">-eq</span> <span class=\"s1\">&#39;True&#39;</span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"enumerate-uac-values-for-admin-users\">Enumerate UAC Values for Admin Users</h3>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nb\">Get-ADUser</span> <span class=\"n\">-Filter</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"n\">adminCount</span> <span class=\"o\">-gt</span> <span class=\"n\">0</span><span class=\"p\">}</span> <span class=\"n\">-Properties</span> <span class=\"n\">admincount</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"n\">useraccountcontrol</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"get-ad-groups-via-wmi\">Get AD Groups via WMI</h3>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nb\">Get-WmiObject</span> <span class=\"n\">-Class</span> <span class=\"n\">win32_group</span> <span class=\"n\">-Filter</span> <span class=\"s2\">&quot;Domain=&#39;&lt;DOMAIN&gt;&#39;&quot;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"search-for-all-computers-adsi\">Search for All Computers (ADSI)</h3>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">[adsisearcher]</span><span class=\"s2\">&quot;(&amp;(objectClass=Computer))&quot;</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">FindAll</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<hr />\n<h2 id=\"windapsearch-python\">windapsearch (Python)</h2>\n<p>Anonymous enumeration of domain users.</p>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code>./windapsearch.py<span class=\"w\"> </span>--dc-ip<span class=\"w\"> </span>&lt;dc-ip&gt;<span class=\"w\"> </span>-u<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">&quot;&quot;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-U\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Authenticated enumeration - Domain Admins:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code>python3<span class=\"w\"> </span>windapsearch.py<span class=\"w\"> </span>--dc-ip<span class=\"w\"> </span>&lt;dc-ip&gt;<span class=\"w\"> </span>-u<span class=\"w\"> </span>&lt;domain&gt;<span class=\"se\">\\&lt;</span>username&gt;<span class=\"w\"> </span>-p<span class=\"w\"> </span>&lt;password&gt;<span class=\"w\"> </span>--da\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Recursive privileged user search:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code>python3<span class=\"w\"> </span>windapsearch.py<span class=\"w\"> </span>--dc-ip<span class=\"w\"> </span>&lt;dc-ip&gt;<span class=\"w\"> </span>-u<span class=\"w\"> </span>&lt;domain&gt;<span class=\"se\">\\&lt;</span>username&gt;<span class=\"w\"> </span>-p<span class=\"w\"> </span>&lt;password&gt;<span class=\"w\"> </span>-PU\n</code></pre></div>\n<hr />\n<h2 id=\"adidnsdump\">adidnsdump</h2>\n<p>Resolve all DNS records in a zone over LDAP. Useful for mapping the internal network from unauthenticated or limited-privilege positions.</p>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code>adidnsdump<span class=\"w\"> </span>-u<span class=\"w\"> </span>&lt;domain&gt;<span class=\"se\">\\\\</span>&lt;username&gt;<span class=\"w\"> </span>ldap://&lt;dc-ip&gt;\nadidnsdump<span class=\"w\"> </span>-u<span class=\"w\"> </span>&lt;domain&gt;<span class=\"se\">\\\\</span>&lt;username&gt;<span class=\"w\"> </span>ldap://&lt;dc-ip&gt;<span class=\"w\"> </span>-r\n</code></pre></div>", "excerpt": "LDAP Enumeration LDAP queries for enumerating Active Directory objects from both Linux and Windows. From Linux (ldapsearch) Enumerate Password Policy ldapsearch -h &lt;dc-ip&gt; -x -b &quot;DC=&lt;DOM", "tags": []}